{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/gamedev/overload-godot","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Godot version</h2>\n<p>A prototype here made with Godot 3.1.</p>\n<p>I believe Astatix came out with this idea first. On their website <a href=\"http://www.astatix.com/overload.php\">http://www.astatix.com/overload.php</a> one can found the original game rules as I remember this game.</p>\n<h2>Experiments with 3D</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/fcb9b3c4b6770772681aadc80c46073c/18539/overload-godot-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Just chips on the board\"\n        title=\"Just chips on the board\"\n        src=\"/static/fcb9b3c4b6770772681aadc80c46073c/5a190/overload-godot-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/fcb9b3c4b6770772681aadc80c46073c/772e8/overload-godot-1.png 200w,\n/static/fcb9b3c4b6770772681aadc80c46073c/e17e5/overload-godot-1.png 400w,\n/static/fcb9b3c4b6770772681aadc80c46073c/5a190/overload-godot-1.png 800w,\n/static/fcb9b3c4b6770772681aadc80c46073c/18539/overload-godot-1.png 1074w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>So first, I implemented basic logic of this game. There are few players with starting chips, each of them make a turn by putting new chip on existing one. When a stack reaches four chips, each chip moves to the nearest cells on the board.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/38a4b7660e6ba336468a16daf3d02fa5/25c1c/overload-godot-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Adjusting colors\"\n        title=\"Adjusting colors\"\n        src=\"/static/38a4b7660e6ba336468a16daf3d02fa5/5a190/overload-godot-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/38a4b7660e6ba336468a16daf3d02fa5/772e8/overload-godot-2.png 200w,\n/static/38a4b7660e6ba336468a16daf3d02fa5/e17e5/overload-godot-2.png 400w,\n/static/38a4b7660e6ba336468a16daf3d02fa5/5a190/overload-godot-2.png 800w,\n/static/38a4b7660e6ba336468a16daf3d02fa5/25c1c/overload-godot-2.png 1047w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Then I have started playing with colors. I chose pastel tones maybe being under impression of pixel art. I looked at the initial board - flat polygon of solid color - and begun to look for ways of adding distinct edges for each cell. To see clearly cells on the board is tactically important in this game.\nI found cool space bar scene (<a href=\"https://free3d.com/3d-model/vega-strike-starship-bar-economy-class-88446.html\">here</a>), but was scared by amount of textures, materials and light that I have to fix after import.\nInstead I expected to incorporate the board into landscape. That way of thinking brings me to Synthwave (<a href=\"https://creativemarket.com/dennybusyet/2289747-Synthwave-Retrowave-Background-Pack\">example</a>).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a041b6218c475179eb79ec1fdf2f394f/d9199/overload-godot-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.49999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Synthwave landscape\"\n        title=\"Synthwave landscape\"\n        src=\"/static/a041b6218c475179eb79ec1fdf2f394f/5a190/overload-godot-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a041b6218c475179eb79ec1fdf2f394f/772e8/overload-godot-3.png 200w,\n/static/a041b6218c475179eb79ec1fdf2f394f/e17e5/overload-godot-3.png 400w,\n/static/a041b6218c475179eb79ec1fdf2f394f/5a190/overload-godot-3.png 800w,\n/static/a041b6218c475179eb79ec1fdf2f394f/d9199/overload-godot-3.png 960w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I followed <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hnLsktA4gmY\">a tutorial</a> on YouTube about how to create Synthwave landscape in Blender.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8563852f7514cc0c559020006610b703/e3189/overload-godot-4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Import landscape to Godot\"\n        title=\"Import landscape to Godot\"\n        src=\"/static/8563852f7514cc0c559020006610b703/5a190/overload-godot-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8563852f7514cc0c559020006610b703/772e8/overload-godot-4.png 200w,\n/static/8563852f7514cc0c559020006610b703/e17e5/overload-godot-4.png 400w,\n/static/8563852f7514cc0c559020006610b703/5a190/overload-godot-4.png 800w,\n/static/8563852f7514cc0c559020006610b703/e3189/overload-godot-4.png 1035w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>When I imported it to Godot, I needed to play with Environment settings and Material to make it look at least close to the rendered picture from the tutorial.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b980cb1d97e99e059a68914d15ef7c5b/58fee/overload-godot-5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"New form and textur of chips\"\n        title=\"New form and textur of chips\"\n        src=\"/static/b980cb1d97e99e059a68914d15ef7c5b/5a190/overload-godot-5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b980cb1d97e99e059a68914d15ef7c5b/772e8/overload-godot-5.png 200w,\n/static/b980cb1d97e99e059a68914d15ef7c5b/e17e5/overload-godot-5.png 400w,\n/static/b980cb1d97e99e059a68914d15ef7c5b/5a190/overload-godot-5.png 800w,\n/static/b980cb1d97e99e059a68914d15ef7c5b/58fee/overload-godot-5.png 1051w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>After I found some balance in glowing parameters, I continued my experiments with 3D objects. As my next target the chips were chosen. I spent a lot of time searching for a good free model of a chip with some interesting ornament on the edge. Nothing for free. So I made one by myself. All together with my texturing skills these cookies are not good.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 800px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/d9ed0/overload-godot-6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 73.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Add shaders to chips\"\n        title=\"Add shaders to chips\"\n        src=\"/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/5a190/overload-godot-6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/772e8/overload-godot-6.png 200w,\n/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/e17e5/overload-godot-6.png 400w,\n/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/5a190/overload-godot-6.png 800w,\n/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/c1b63/overload-godot-6.png 1200w,\n/static/6b6737f77bf58625b2c06c9ee4f33521/d9ed0/overload-godot-6.png 1415w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>But I continued playing with them. I shall tell you that they are ugly, just because they are not finished. Thus I am adding a shader to make them look like crystals (inspired by <a href=\"https://80.lv/articles/developing-artistic-ice-in-unreal-engine-4/\">this</a>, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7m7_lhrXJ08&#x26;t=2s\">this</a> and <a href=\"https://bobacupcake.itch.io/so-chunks-huh\">this</a>). </p>\n<p>I said, they are crystals!</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/mikolasan/overload-godot\">Here</a> you can convince me to change license from GPL 3 to MIT. </p>","frontmatter":{"date":"August 07, 2020","path":"/gamedev/overload-godot","title":"Overload","draft":null,"subtitle":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":3.4909090909090907,"src":"/static/af2b67a485ddc09822597be5a71d8735/b053d/overload-godot-code.png","srcSet":"/static/af2b67a485ddc09822597be5a71d8735/e3208/overload-godot-code.png 576w,\n/static/af2b67a485ddc09822597be5a71d8735/e1d67/overload-godot-code.png 768w,\n/static/af2b67a485ddc09822597be5a71d8735/812f0/overload-godot-code.png 922w,\n/static/af2b67a485ddc09822597be5a71d8735/b053d/overload-godot-code.png 1380w","sizes":"(max-width: 1380px) 100vw, 1380px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"pagePath":"/gamedev/overload-godot","breadcrumb":{"location":"/gamedev/overload-godot","crumbs":[{"pathname":"/","crumbLabel":"Index"},{"pathname":"/gamedev","crumbLabel":"gamedev"},{"pathname":"/gamedev/overload-godot","crumbLabel":"overload-godot"}]}}}}